                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="altman_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">(1920-2006) a US film director. His films usually gave a sad or funny picture of US life. They include <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/m-a-s-h" title="M*A*S*H definition"><span class="ndv">M*A*S*H</span></a> (1970), <span class="ebi">Nashville</span> (1975), <span class="ebi">Short Cuts</span> (1995), based on stories by <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/raymond-carver" title="Raymond Carver definition"><span class="ndv">Raymond Carver</span></a>, and <span class="ebi">Gosford Park</span> (2001) which is set in an English <span class="ndv" xt="andv" tofix="" href="countryhouse_d_1">country house</span>.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
